# Environment variable template for Ball Knowledge.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to ".env"  ->  cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in real values in ".env" (that file is git-ignored and never pushed).
#   3. Restart the dev server after changing .env (Vite only reads it on startup).
#
# IMPORTANT - this is a frontend-only Vite app:
#   - Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are visible to the app code
#     (access them via import.meta.env.VITE_SOMETHING).
#   - ANY VITE_ value is bundled into the browser JavaScript and is therefore
#     readable by users. Do NOT put real/private secrets here. Use this only for
#     non-sensitive config or values that are meant to be public.
#   - True secrets (private API keys, DB passwords) require a backend and must
#     not live in this app at all.

# Example (replace or remove):
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=
# VITE_PUBLIC_KEY=
